com.amazon.device.ads

Class AdSize

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.amazon.device.ads.AdSize

  • public class AdSize
extends java.lang.Object
    Ad sizes supported by the Amazon Mobile Ads API. Dimensions are in device independent pixels, therefore the actual size of the ad in pixels might vary depending on the resolution of the device. Ads will scale accordingly within your ad view container to accommodate varying device resolutions.

      • SIZE_AUTO_NO_SCALE

        public static final AdSize SIZE_AUTO_NO_SCALE
        Defines an ad to be sized automatically, but not to scale the ad up to fit the container it is in. The ad will display no larger than its true device-independent pixel size. In most cases the ad will display at its exact device-independent pixel scale, but in some special cases it may downscale slightly.

    • Method Detail

      • newGravity

        public AdSize newGravity(int gravity)
        Creates a copy of this AdSize but with the layout gravity changed to the value provided. If the ad is not scaling to fill its container (for example, if the size is set to SIZE_AUTO_NO_SCALE) then this method will set the ad's layout gravity. Defaults to CENTER. Note that the gravity will have no effect on the ad's placement in cases where the ad scales to fill its container. Note that the method does not alter this AdSize object, but creates a new one that is returned.
        Parameters:
        gravity - the gravity setting to use (see android.view.Gravity)
        Returns:
        a new AdSize cloned from this one, but with the gravity changed to the value provided
